Package: ggcollapse
Title: an R package to collapse nodes using ggtree
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("MoisÃ¨s", "Bernabeu", , "moises.bernabeu.sci@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0498-5957"))
Description: This package contains a set of functions that expand the `ggtree` package. The main function of this set, `ggcollapse` allows the user to collapse nodes with the same height for the collapsing triangles. The package also contains some functions that help in the task of finding monophyletic groups of a certain taxonomic rank and the full set of sister clades to a given node.
Imports:
    treeio (>= 1.28.0),
    ape (>= 5.8),
    phytools (>= 2.3.0),
    ggtree (>= 3.13.1),
    methods (>= 4.4.1)
